Cleanup Begins Ahead of Spring Flood at Dakota Pipeline Protest Sites Tensions still run high as Trump administration moves toward approval of project By @wconnors Feb. 1, 2017 3:34 p.m. ET 
CHICAGO—A cleanup of the main campsite of protesters opposed to the Dakota Access Pipeline began this week, as law-enforcement officials and protesters agree to move to safety ahead of spring flooding. But the Trump administration’s push to approve the pipeline project means that many protesters aren’t likely to leave altogether.
